        <!-- NEW: Version 4.0.5 - 18 July 2026 -->
        <div class="version">
            <h3>📱 Version 4.0.5 - Report Tabs, Passenger Editor, Mobile Zoom & More</h3>
            <div class="date">Released: 18 July 2026</div>
            
            <div class="feature">
                <span class="feature-badge">FEATURE</span>
                <strong>Multiple Report Tabs</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Generate multiple reports and keep them all open in separate tabs</li>
                    <li>Each tab stores its own manifest, passenger data, and all edits</li>
                    <li>Switch between tabs instantly – perfect for comparing two flights or services</li>
                    <li>Tabs persist across browser sessions (saved in localStorage)</li>
                    <li>Delete unwanted tabs with a confirmation dialog</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="feature">
                <span class="feature-badge">FEATURE</span>
                <strong>Passenger Card Editor</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Tap any seat in the report (or the seat number in the passenger card) to open an editing panel</li>
                    <li>Edit special assistance codes: DEPO, MAAS, MEDA, NTL, UM, VVIP, WCHC, WCHR, WCHS, YPTA, or “Others” with free‑text</li>
                    <li>Toggle <strong>INF</strong> (Infant) and <strong>EXT</strong> (Extension Seatbelt) flags</li>
                    <li>Add or modify free‑text <strong>Remarks</strong></li>
                    <li>All changes are saved across tabs and persist in localStorage</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="feature">
                <span class="feature-badge">FEATURE</span>
                <strong>Seat Reassignment via On‑Screen Keypad</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Long‑press any seat cell in the main report or tap the ✎ icon in the passenger card to change a passenger’s seat</li>
                    <li>Keypad lets you enter a new seat number (row + letter)</li>
                    <li>If the new seat is already taken, a conflict warning appears and both passengers are shown – you can then reassign the other passenger</li>
                    <li>Changes are reflected immediately in the report and the seat lookup modal</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="improvement">
                <span class="improvement-badge">IMPROVEMENT</span>
                <strong>Summary Bar Pills Now Only Show Non‑Zero Counts</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Previously all four pills (SPECIAL, INF, EXT, REMARKS) were shown even with zero counts, cluttering the interface</li>
                    <li>Now only categories with at least one passenger appear, keeping the summary bar clean and useful</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="improvement">
                <span class="improvement-badge">IMPROVEMENT</span>
                <strong>UI Alignment – Tabs & Summary Bar</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Report tabs and summary bar now have the same left/right padding (20 px) as the Generate Report button and input section</li>
                    <li>Consistent visual alignment across all elements</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="improvement">
                <span class="improvement-badge">IMPROVEMENT</span>
                <strong>Mobile Pinch‑to‑Zoom Enabled</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Removed <code>maximum-scale=1.0</code> and <code>user-scalable=no</code> from the viewport meta tag</li>
                    <li>Users can now zoom in on any part of the page on Android Chrome, iOS Safari, and other mobile browsers</li>
                    <li>Does not affect the Print Scale slider or print settings – they remain independent</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Version 4.0.4 - 2 June 2026 -->
        <div class="version">
            <h3>🪑 Version 4.0.4 - 737 Business Class Row 4 Toggle</h3>
            <div class="date">Released: 2 June 2026</div>
            
            <div class="feature">
                <span class="feature-badge">FEATURE</span>
                <strong>Toggle Between 3‑Row and 4‑Row Business Class Layouts</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>New button in 737 seat chart control bar to switch between 3 rows (737NG/MAX) and 4 rows (737NR)</li>
                    <li>When switching to 3‑row mode, row 4 is completely removed (not just hidden) to match actual aircraft configuration</li>
                    <li>If any passengers are assigned to row 4, a temporary warning appears in the zone summary</li>
                    <li>Passenger data is preserved and repopulated when toggling back to 4‑row mode</li>
                    <li>Works seamlessly with Aft View and font size adjustments</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="improvement">
                <span class="improvement-badge">IMPROVEMENT</span>
                <strong>Improved 737 Seat Chart Flexibility</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Crew can now match the exact business class row count of the aircraft (3 rows for NG/MAX, 4 rows for NR)</li>
                    <li>Prevents confusion of seeing an extra blank row when row 4 is not present</li>
                    <li><i>"Reduces paper and ink usage by removing unnecessary rows when printing"</i> - Fahrin</li>
                    <li>Regeneration logic preserves existing chart data and aft view orientation</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="info">
                <span class="info-badge">NOTE</span>
                <strong>How It Works</strong>
                <p style="margin-top: 6px;">The 737 seat chart now has a checkbox labeled “4‑Row Mode (737NR)” – checked = 4 rows, unchecked = 3 rows. When unchecked, the seat grid regenerates with only rows 1–3. Any passengers originally seated in row 4 will not be displayed, and a warning appears. Re‑checking the box restores row 4 and all passengers. This gives crews full control to match the actual aircraft they are working on.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Version 4.0.3 - Birthday Detection -->
        <div class="version">
            <h3>🎂 Version 4.0.3 - Birthday Detection displayed using 🎂</h3>
            <div class="date">Released: 27 May 2026</div>
            
            <div class="feature">
                <span class="feature-badge">FEATURE</span>
                <strong>Passenger Birthday Detection</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Detects passenger birthdays from manifest PAX DOB lines (<code>DD/MM</code> format)</li>
                    <li>Identifies birthdays on the flight date or the next day (for long-haul flights crossing midnight)</li>
                    <li>Adds 🎂 icon in meal column and summary counters</li>
                    <li>Birthday passengers automatically included in filtered reports (even without special meals or elite tier)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="improvement">
                <span class="improvement-badge">IMPROVEMENT</span>
                <strong>Enhanced Parsing & Summary Integration</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Added <code>DOB_PATTERN</code> to correctly skip date lines without affecting passenger name</li>
                    <li>Birthday counts now appear in Global Summary, Zone Summary, and Port/Starboard side stats</li>
                    <li>Seat chart also shows 🎂 next to meal (if present) or standalone for business class passengers</li>
                    <li>Helps crew offer card, keychain etc. on board</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="info">
                <span class="info-badge">NOTE</span>
                <strong>Birthday Check Logic</strong>
                <p style="margin-top: 6px;">Birthday is considered valid if the passenger’s <code>DD/MM</code> matches either the flight date or the following day – useful for long-haul flights where the meal service may occur after midnight local time. Do note that PAX DOB column in BPM is live and only display the birthdate according to real date(today) and the day after(tomorrow).</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
